name: Wounded
description:
Summoning Instinct


I will always refuge in nature
like any other wounded animal.
So the sea licks my wounds
may the wind pushes my breathe,
letting the sun shine inside
more than outside.
May the moon listens my howl...
 
I will always refuge in that sacred place
intangible, dreamlike, warm
real home
There I pray to the ancient gods,
those that my savages words,
make no justice.
I trust
they can save me.
 
I will always refuge in the earthship
holding on the roots
of the most survivor tree.
This dying pray…
waits the echo comes back electric
in the mighty way of
another heartbeat.
